                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112A European War 1939/35037:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-17T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 17, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1041. Your 1369, August 14. You are authorized to inform appropriate Bolivian
                    officials informally that while adoption of proposed law is, of course, a matter
                    for the Bolivian Government to decide, its passage would probably in large part
                    render unnecessary United States financial aid which was based on the assumption
                    of replacement of leading Axis firms seemingly exempted by proposed law.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
